The paper deals with the problem of planar graph isomorphism and canonization, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper presents a logspace algorithm for planar graph canonization, which involves constructing the biconnected component tree and refining each biconnected component into a triconnected component tree. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Machine Learning (cs.LG), as these categories are closely related to the problem of graph isomorphism and canonization.
